dct_title_s: A new map of Michigan with its canals, roads & distances; by H.S. Tanner.
dct_description_sm: Prime meridian: Washington. Engraved by: E.B. Dawson. From: Tanner's universal atlas, no. 25. Below border at left: "Entered according to act of Congress, in the year 1833, by H.S. Tanner, in the clerk's office of the Eastern District of Pennsylvania." Includes table of steam boat routes. Shows county divisions. 1 map: col.; 33 x 27 cm. This map is in the public domain. Please attribute access and use of this digitized map to the Stephen S. Clark Library, University of Michigan Library.
dct_creator_sm: Tanner, Henry Schenck, 1786-1858.,Dawson, E. B., engineer.,Dahl, James, former owner.
